👑Royal Variety Performance 👑
Raising funds for the Royal Variety Charity.

My french master clown teacher Philippe Gaulier always said “The Clown must always look to the audience to see if the King Of Sweden is there!”
Of course it’s just a silly metaphor for remembering to really see the audience. But hey, the King Of Sweden’s daughter was actually there that night! 😂 

Luckily it wasn’t so hard to see the audience… Never seen so many posh people in Hi Vis in my life 😄

I dedicate this performance to my parents and partner who were all there on the special night at Royal Albert Hall.

Thank you to my partner, whom I love more than anything in this world ❤️

Friends and family might even spotted my dad in the audience?!
 
And a special thank you to the one who did the most for my career and made me the person I am today, my mother Anne Marie Stensrud, who believed in me when no one else did (myself included). She taught me the importance of never giving up and just go for it One More Time 😃❤️
